Title
Comparison engine decomposition and module boundary cleanup

Role
BUILDER

Objective
Decompose the oversized comparison engine into smaller, typed, reviewable modules now that output contracts and schemas have been repaired by prior hardening work.

This packet exists because the comparison engine is currently too large and too layered to review safely. Even if its outputs are now typed and schema-backed, the implementation remains structurally fragile if core logic is concentrated in a monolithic engine.

This is a decomposition and maintainability packet.
It is not a methodology-redesign packet.

